It is a shorthand assignment operator. It takes the following form:
   
    variable op= expression;

is short form of

    variable = variable op expression;

So, 

    density *= invertedRatio;

is equivalent to

    density = density * invertedRatio;

See the following link for more info:

[How to Use Assignment Operators in Java][1]


  [1]: http://www.ehow.com/how_2094990_use-assignment-operators-java.html

